    "FR-NET-0013","`src/lib/nogc_async_mut/io/connection_pool.spl`","`src/lib/nogc_async_mut/io/connection_pool.spl`","`src/lib/nogc_async_mut/io/connection_pool.spl`","Add TCP connection pool for HTTP keep-alive reuse","Provide a pure Simple connection pool keyed by host:port that tracks idle file descriptors with timestamps, enforces max-idle-per-host, and exposes acquire/release/evict-expired operations. Pool stats (acquired, released, evicted) must be i","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/net_acceleration_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/net_connect_completion.md`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-05-10","2026-05-10",true
    "FR-STORAGE-0001","storage__(src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/fat32_stub.spl_→_fat32.spl)","storage__(src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/fat32_stub.spl_→_fat32.spl)","storage  (src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/fat32_stub.spl → fat32.spl)","Fat32Driver: statfs() and truncate/ftruncate not implemented","`Fat32Driver.statfs()` currently returns `pass_todo`. The missing piece is in `src/os/services/fat32/fat32.spl` (class `Fat32Driver`): after `mount()` the geometry fields (`total_clusters`, `sectors_per_cluster`, `bytes_per_sector`) are pop","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/storage_fat32_statfs_truncate.md`;","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-17","2026-04-17",true
    "FR-STORAGE-0002","storage__(src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/fat32_stub.spl_→_fat32.spl)","storage__(src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/fat32_stub.spl_→_fat32.spl)","storage  (src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/fat32_stub.spl → fat32.spl)","Fat32Driver: true pread/pwrite (cursor-preserving positional I/O)","`FsDriver.pread(handle, offset, buf)` must not advance the file cursor — it is a POSIX `pread(2)` semantics requirement. The current `Fat32Driver` in `src/os/services/fat32/fat32.spl` lacks cursor-save/restore around seek+read. `Fat32OpenFi","current","P2","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/storage_fat32_positional_cursor.md`;","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-17","2026-04-17",true
    "FR-STORAGE-0003","storage__(src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/fat32_stub.spl_→_fat32.spl)","storage__(src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/fat32_stub.spl_→_fat32.spl)","storage  (src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/fat32_stub.spl → fat32.spl)","Fat32Driver: fstat(FileHandle) and readdir(DirHandle) via handle","`FsDriver.fstat(FileHandle)` and `FsDriver.readdir(DirHandle)` both receive opaque handles, not paths. The wrapper in `fat32_stub.spl` maintains a `file_handles: [Fat32HandleEntry]` table with `path: text` per entry, so the information is p","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/storage_fat32_handle_metadata.md`;","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-17","2026-04-17",true
    "FR-STORAGE-0004","nvfs","nvfs","nvfs","MountTable.resolve() uses slice() which is broken in baremetal Cranelift","Rewrite `MountTable.resolve(path)` in `src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/fs_driver/mount_table.spl:129` so it does NOT call `path.raw.slice(mp_len, …)`. Cranelift's baremetal codegen has a known-broken `slice()` operation (per the hazard comment already in `shell_serial_entry.spl`); any baremetal caller routed through the mount ta","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/fs_driver_interface.md §2` (MountTable contract), `doc/05_design/simpleos_fs_migration.md §M2` (the retrofit this blocks)","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-HOT-001","simple_db__(examples/11_advanced/simple_db/src/engine/hot.spl)","simple_db__(examples/11_advanced/simple_db/src/engine/hot.spl)","Simple DB  (examples/11_advanced/simple_db/src/engine/hot.spl)","HOT: integrate pd_upper/pd_lower free-space check before chaining","`HotChain.try_update` currently chains a HOT update unconditionally at the logical-page-group level. A real PostgreSQL HOT update is only valid when the page has sufficient free space (pd_upper − pd_lower > tuple_size). The","current","P2","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`examples/11_advanced/simple_db/doc/design/hot_update.md` (M3a design)","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-17","2026-04-17",true
    "FR-BENCH-CLOCK-002","nvfs","nvfs","nvfs","Replace PIT-ch2 TSC calibration with HPET/PMTMR","Current TSC calibration in `src/os/kernel/arch/x86_64/timer.spl` uses PIT channel 2 for a ~10ms measurement window. Virtualised QEMU HPET is available via the ACPI HPET table (MMIO counter at 100 MHz-ish) and provides better","current","P2","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/simpleos_fs_migration.md` (boot init section)","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-SIMPLEOS-ACPI-001","os__(src/os/kernel/acpi/)","os__(src/os/kernel/acpi/)","os  (src/os/kernel/acpi/)","ACPI table walker (RSDP → RSDT/XSDT → FADT + HPET)","SimpleOS needs real HPET MMIO base and PMTMR I/O port from ACPI tables so that TSC calibration can use sub-0.1% reference sources instead of PIT-ch2.","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/simpleos_fs_migration.md` (boot init section)","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-SIMPLEOS-M5-001","os__(src/os/services/vfs/vfs_init.spl)","os__(src/os/services/vfs/vfs_init.spl)","os  (src/os/services/vfs/vfs_init.spl)","VFS select-file cursor semantic (VfsCursor singleton)","`rt_fat32_select_file` (retired in M5) held a static 64-byte name cursor that callers used to remember the last-selected file before operating on it.","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/fs_driver_interface.md §3`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-NVFS-N4a-001","nvfs","nvfs","nvfs","Scrub repair path: detect + repair from reflink peers","`scrub_all` previously only detected checksum mismatches and reported them. Add a repair path: when a bad block is found, scan all pmap sidecar entries for a peer whose stored checksum matches the bad entry's expected checksum and","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design_v2.md §14`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-NVFS-N4b-001","nvfs","nvfs","nvfs","Proactive scrub scheduler + META_DURABLE replica repair","N4a repair falls back to Unrepairable when no reflink peer has a good copy. N4b should (a) add a background-task scheduler that runs `scrub_all` periodically (honouring `throttle_ms`), and (b) extend the repair path to","current","P2","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design_v2.md §14`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-N3-001","nvfs","nvfs","nvfs","Replace flat pmap sidecar with B-tree keyed by (arena_id, offset)","The flat `_pmap_sidecar: [PmapSidecarEntry]` in `fs_driver_impl.spl` performs O(n) linear scan on every read and write path.  Replace it with a B-tree keyed by `(arena_id, offset)` so that insert and lookup are O(log n).  The B-tree must su","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design_v2.md §17`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-17","2026-04-17",true
    "FR-NVFS-N5b-001","nvfs","nvfs","nvfs","B-tree rebalancing on delete (merge / rotate)","`pmap_btree_remove` in N5a performs leaf-only deletion without rebalancing. After many deletes the tree can become unbalanced (under-filled nodes). Implement standard B-tree merge and rotation on delete so the tree remains","current","P2","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design_v2.md §17`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-17","2026-04-17",true
    "FR-BENCH-CLOCK-001","nvfs","nvfs","nvfs","Add rt_time_now_ns() for hosted and baremetal targets","Bench harness in `test/05_perf/bench/lib/timing.spl` calls `extern fn rt_time_now_ns() -> i64` but the symbol was absent from both hosted and baremetal runtimes. Hosted: backed by `clock_gettime(CLOCK_MONOTONIC)`.","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/08_tracking/bench/README.md`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-17","2026-04-17",true
    "FR-NVFS-N6a-001","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/encryption.spl)","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/encryption.spl)","nvfs  (src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/encryption.spl)","Wire real AES-128-GCM into NVFS leaf DEK encrypt/decrypt","`encryption.spl` stubs (`_aes128_encrypt_stub` / `_aes128_decrypt_stub`) use XOR + checksum instead of real AES-128-GCM. Replace with calls to","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design_v2.md §14`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-17","2026-04-17",true
    "FR-NVFS-N6a-002","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/encryption.spl)","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/encryption.spl)","nvfs  (src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/encryption.spl)","KDF hardening: salted derivation for per-arena dataset keys","`_derive_data_key_bytes` used a plain XOR of master_key bytes and arena_id with no domain separation or salt. Upgrade to a salted derivation that includes","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design_v2.md §14`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-NVFS-N6a-003","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/encryption.spl_+_arena.spl)","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/encryption.spl_+_arena.spl)","nvfs  (src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/encryption.spl + arena.spl)","DEK rotation on arena seal","On `arena_seal_impl`, if the arena is registered as encrypted in the `EncryptionInfo` registry, derive a fresh DEK (bumped generation) and update","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design_v2.md §14`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-NVFS-N6b-001","nvfs","nvfs","nvfs","Raw send / encrypted replication stream (btrfs-send style)","Stream a sealed MODEL_IMMUTABLE arena between peers without decrypting the payload.  Ciphertext + key metadata travel over the wire as a self-describing byte stream (magic `NVSR`, 16-byte header, per-arena begin/extent/end records).","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs/send_format.md`; `nvfs_design_v2.md §14`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-NVFS-N7a-001","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/compression.spl_—_new)","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/compression.spl_—_new)","nvfs  (src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/compression.spl — new)","Inline compression: per-arena LZ4/Zstd, class-aware defaults","Add an inline compression layer (N7a) between the logical block and the physical device. Compression is per-dataset, per-arena, and opt-in via mount option `compress=<algo>`","current","P2","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design.md §V3-2, §V3-5, §V3-6, §V3-7`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-NVFS-N7b-001","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/dedup.spl_—_new)","nvfs__(src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/dedup.spl_—_new)","nvfs  (src/os/services/nvfs/src/core/dedup.spl — new)","Inline deduplication: content-addressable DDT extending reflink machinery","Add an inline deduplication layer (N7b) backed by a content-addressable Deduplication Table (DDT). The DDT maps `content_hash (u8[32]) → DedupEntry` where DedupEntry carries the canonical logical_page_no, birth_gen, refcount, and flags (56 ","current","P2","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design.md §V3-3, §V3-4, §V3-6, §V3-7`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-BDD-WAVE7-8-001","test/fixtures/features/","test/fixtures/features/","test/fixtures/features/","BDD feature files for wave 7/8 storage work","MDSOC+ requires BDD specs for new functionality before or alongside impl. Wave 7/8 added AES-GCM encryption (N6a), raw send/receive (N6b), scrub detect+repair","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design_v2.md §14`, `doc/05_design/nvfs_design.md`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
    "FR-SPOSTGRE-M4-001","simple_db__(examples/11_advanced/simple_db/src/engine/tier_cache.spl)","simple_db__(examples/11_advanced/simple_db/src/engine/tier_cache.spl)","Simple DB  (examples/11_advanced/simple_db/src/engine/tier_cache.spl)","L2 NVMe tier cache (Aurora Optimized Reads pattern)","When a clean DRAM page is about to be evicted from `BufferPool`, write it to a DB_TEMP arena on local NVMe instead of discarding it. On subsequent page fault,","current","P1","doc/08_tracking/feature/nvfs_requests.md","","","","","`doc/05_design/nvfs_design.md §DB_TEMP`","","","","","","","","","","","2026-04-18","2026-04-18",true
